2021-12-05

Future Predicted Value

Future predicted value is the estimate of how much someone will spend in the future with a company. In this report we calculate FPV for the Wedge in 2015 using data from before that year. Our report has the following sections:

  1. Variable selection: In this section we describe the variables that we use in the model.
  2. Model formulation: This section describes the model itself.
  3. Estimates of model accuracy: We run a quick analysis of model accuracy in the final section.

Q2:Do a short write up of your model. What terms are significant? Whats the R^2? Whats the residual standard error and how would you interpret it?

The sales of 2014 is very significant to the model, an adjusted r-squared of 77.60% reveals that 77.60% of the data fit the regression model. Residual Standard Error is measure of the quality of a linear regression fit. In our example, the actual sales in 2015 can deviate from the true regression line by approximately 1491 dollars, on average.
